{{For|the film|Helpline (film)}} A '''helpline''' is a [[telephone]] service which offers help to those who call. Many helpline services now offer more than telephone support - offering access to information, advice or customer service via telephone, email, web or SMS.<ref>{{cite web|title=Definition of Helpline|url=http://www.dictionary.com/browse/helpline|publisher=[[Dictionary.com]]|accessdate=14 December 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=What is a Helpline?|url=http://www.ifotes.org/emotional-support/what-is-a-helpline|publisher=[[Volunteer Emotional Support Helplines#IFOTES - International Federation of Telephone Emergency Services]]|accessdate=13 January 2017}}</ref> The word ''[[hotline]]'' is also sometimes used to refer to a helpline. A helpline can provide emotional support to person in distress in its minimalistic form. It may help the individual
Services include * [[User Assistance]] (for example computer software support) * [[telephone counseling]], [[medical hotlines]], [[insolvency hotlines]], [[crisis hotline]]s and many other types of hotlines.
