===United Kingdom===

From 1988 to 1994,<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/uk/broadcasters-welcome-end-to-censorship-1449238.html|title=Broadcasters welcome end to 'censorship'|last=Williams|first=Rhys|date=16 September 1994|work=The Independent|access-date=2017-03-15|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161009192834/http://www.independent.co.uk/news/uk/broadcasters-welcome-end-to-censorship-1449238.html|archive-date=2016-10-09|dead-url=no|language=en-GB|df=}}</ref> the United Kingdom [[1988‚Äì94 British broadcasting voice restrictions|banned broadcasting of the voices]] of people linked to [[the Troubles|violence in Northern Ireland]]; television circumvented this using actors' voices synchronized to footage of prohibited people speaking.

===United States===
{{main article|Voice acting in the United States}}
